\cf0 (Q)\'a0: LaTeXiT does not work under MacOS 10.7 Lion.\
(A)\'a0: LaTeXiT is fully compatible with MacOS 10.7 Lion. But the following scenario may occur\'a0: you might have, a long time ago, configured LaTeXiT to use a PowerPC vesion of the LaTeX engine. ANd Lion does not allow PowerPC code any more. Please check your LaTeX installation, and the paths to pdflatex in the LaTeXiT's preferences ("Composition" pane).\
\
(Q)\'a0: LaTeXiT is crashing at each latexization.";\
(A)\'a0: LaTeXiT is theoretically fully 64 bits compatible. But some buggy 64 bits components of MacOS 10.4, 10.5 and 10.6, are sometimes responsible for those crashes. In the Finder, "Get info"(Command-i) of LaTeXiT and check "Open in 32-bit mode". If it does not solve the problem, send me the crash log.\
