\fs22 \cf0 \ulnone (Q)\'a0: LinkBack does not work when I use the LaTeXiT's service.\
(A)\'a0: See section "Known issues" for more details. To solve this problem, try to disable the baseline alignment of the equation in the LaTeXiT's service preferences.\
\
(Q)\'a0: I don't understand the "encapsulation" palette.\
(A)\'a0: This palette fills a very particular need. Usually, it is useless to drag'n drop an equation (as an image) towards an application that cannot display images. However, if this application is a LaTeX text editor, it may be relevant to drag'n drop some text related to the equation : its source code, a \\ref\{\} with its title.... So, this is customizable in the palette, and will work for drag'n drop from the library.\
\
(Q)\'a0: How can I use the feynmf package with LaTeXiT ?\
(A)\'a0:  You should use the feynmp package, in "Text" LaTeX mode, using a "latex+dvipdf" composition. Then, a middle-processing script is needed to compute the metafonts of the labels; you should define the following middle-processing script :\
				mpost the-name-of-your-feynmf-graph\
				#but now me must recreate the pdf file\
				latex $\{INPUTTEXFILE\}\
				dvipdf $\{OUTPUTDVIFILE\}\
	Please see the previous section "Using scripts" for enhanced explanations.\
        You can also check the web page {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://osksn2.hep.sci.osaka-u.ac.jp/%7Etaku/osx/feynmp_latexit.html"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs24 \cf4 http://osksn2.hep.sci.osaka-u.ac.jp/%7Etaku/osx/feynmp_latexit.html}} (thanks to T. Yamanaka)\
\
